{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769630294,"nonce":"rl/pnkCNqtqnbqO3gOQjj5VA1Rc=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mf-xj","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/110","origin":"github"},"title":"Add \"Continuous Improvement\" workflow for agents to identify and report infrastructure friction","message":"## Problem\n\nAI agents encounter friction points during sessions (unclear docs, missing workflows, confusing scripts) but there's no standardized process for:\n1. Identifying these issues systematically\n2. Capturing them with sufficient context\n3. Opening well-formed improvement issues\n4. Preventing the same friction from affecting future agents\n\nCurrently, friction identification is ad-hoc and relies on humans asking \"what problems did you have?\"\n\n## What We Did (Session 66b4eea3)\n\nUser asked: *\"Reviewing the sessions, what friction have we encountered that could be fixed by improving the agent infrastructure that we haven't reported yet?\"*\n\nAgent process:\n1. ✅ Reviewed session summary and checkpoint history\n2. ✅ Checked existing open issues to avoid duplicates\n3. ✅ Identified 6 friction points with priority/impact analysis\n4. ✅ Opened 3 well-formed issues (#107, #108, #109) with:\n   - Concrete examples from session\n   - Impact assessment\n   - Proposed solutions\n   - Session evidence references\n\n**Result**: 3 actionable improvements that will help all future agents\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nCreate a workflow: `.agent/workflows/ops/continuous-improvement.md`\n\n### When to Run\n- End of significant work sessions\n- After completing major tasks\n- When user asks \"what could be better?\"\n- Periodically (e.g., weekly review by designated agent)\n\n### Process\n\n**Step 1: Identify Friction**\nReview session for:\n- Commands/scripts that didn't work as expected\n- Documentation that was unclear or incomplete\n- Workflows that required workarounds\n- Repetitive manual steps that could be automated\n- Confusing error messages or missing feedback\n- Path/environment issues\n\n**Step 2: Check for Duplicates**\n```bash\ngh issue list --repo rolker/ros2_agent_workspace --state open --limit 50\n```\n\n**Step 3: Prioritize Issues**\n- 🔴 High: Blocks work, affects all agents, safety/correctness issues\n- 🟡 Medium: Reduces efficiency, affects common workflows\n- 🟢 Low: Minor annoyances, rare edge cases\n\n**Step 4: Draft Issues** (show user before creating)\nFor each friction point:\n- **Problem**: What went wrong? What was confusing?\n- **Example**: Concrete command/code that failed or was unclear\n- **Proposed Solution**: Specific fix (script change, doc update, new workflow)\n- **Impact**: Who benefits? How much time saved?\n- **Session Evidence**: Link to checkpoint or session ID\n- **Signature**: AI agent + model\n\n**Step 5: Create Issues**\n```bash\ngh issue create --repo rolker/ros2_agent_workspace \\\n  --title \"...\" \\\n  --label \"enhancement\" \\\n  --body \"...\"\n```\n\n### Template\n\n```markdown\n## Problem\n[What friction was encountered?]\n\n## Example Friction\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n# What the agent tried:\n...\n\n# What should have worked:\n...\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Proposed Solution\n[Specific change to make]\n\n## Impact\n- ✅ Benefit 1\n- ✅ Benefit 2\n\n## Priority\n🔴/🟡/🟢 [High/Medium/Low] - [Why?]\n\n## Session Evidence\nSession: [session-id]\n- [Specific example from session]\n- [What was the workaround?]\n\n---\n**🤖 Reported-By**: [Agent Name] ([Model])\n```\n\n### Integration with CLI_COMMANDS.md\n\nAdd command: `/continuous-improvement` or `/report-friction`\n\n## Benefits\n\n✅ **Systematic improvement** - No friction goes unreported\n✅ **Rich context** - Issues include examples and evidence\n✅ **Prevents regression** - Same problems don't recur\n✅ **Knowledge capture** - Session learnings feed back into system\n✅ **Agent empowerment** - Agents improve their own tools\n✅ **Clear prioritization** - High-impact fixes get attention\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Create `.agent/workflows/ops/continuous-improvement.md`\n- [ ] Add issue template to `.agent/templates/improvement_issue.md`\n- [ ] Add `/continuous-improvement` to CLI_COMMANDS.md\n- [ ] Update CONTRIBUTING.md to encourage friction reporting\n- [ ] Add to AI_RULES.md: \"Report friction at session end\"\n- [ ] Optional: Create script `.agent/scripts/report_friction.sh` (interactive)\n\n## Example Success Criteria\n\nAfter implementing this workflow:\n- Agents proactively identify 2-3 improvements per major session\n- Infrastructure issues are well-formed and actionable\n- Friction points decrease over time (measured by # of new issues of this type)\n- New agents onboard faster due to continuously improving docs\n\n## Related Issues\n- #98 - Make sync-repos discoverable (found via this process)\n- #107 - Model parameter (found via this process)\n- #108 - Testing workflows (found via this process)\n- #109 - PR review workflow (found via this process)\n\n---\n**🤖 Reported-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}